Take this. Put it back.

1254
00:59:34,595 --> 00:59:37,034
If anything happens,
you take this,

1255
00:59:37,136 --> 00:59:39,099
and you stab him
in the neck as hard

1256
00:59:39,201 --> 00:59:40,333
and as fast as you can.

1257
00:59:40,435 --> 00:59:41,630
- No! No, no!
- It has to be you.

1258
00:59:41,732 --> 00:59:42,898
He's watching me too closely.

1259
00:59:43,000 --> 00:59:45,271
- He won't expect us to do it.
- Sister, no!

1260
00:59:45,373 --> 00:59:46,775
Okay. Let's have a code word.

1261
00:59:46,877 --> 00:59:48,110
Okay? Um...

1262
00:59:48,212 --> 00:59:50,077
Hey, if I say
"magic underwear,"

1263
00:59:50,179 --> 00:59:52,008
that means stab. Okay?

1264
00:59:52,784 --> 00:59:53,782
(DISTANT THUD)

1265
00:59:53,884 --> 00:59:55,614
He's coming.

1266
00:59:55,716 --> 00:59:58,315
Magic underwear.
That's the code word. Okay?

1267
00:59:58,417 --> 00:59:59,587
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1268
01:00:02,123 --> 01:00:03,789
(CREAKING)

1269
01:00:04,797 --> 01:00:06,055
(PAXTON WHIMPERS)

1270
01:00:06,996 --> 01:00:08,728
(DOOR UNLOCKS)

1271
01:00:14,333 --> 01:00:15,297
(DOOR OPENS)

1272
01:00:15,400 --> 01:00:17,605
(CREAKING)

1273
01:00:19,636 --> 01:00:22,038
(CREAKING CONTINUES)

1274
01:00:27,980 --> 01:00:30,213
- (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)
- (BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY)

1275
01:00:30,315 --> 01:00:31,520
Mr. Reed?

1276
01:00:32,388 --> 01:00:34,622
(OMINOUS MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING)

1277
01:00:36,994 --> 01:00:39,396
(SQUELCHY FOOTSTEPS)

1278
01:00:41,526 --> 01:00:43,598
(LANTERN CREAKING)

1279
01:00:46,533 --> 01:00:48,669
- (WHIMPERS)
- Mrs. Reed?

1280
01:00:50,336 --> 01:00:51,639
Is that you?

1281
01:00:56,214 --> 01:00:57,975
(OMINOUS MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING)

1282
01:01:06,419 --> 01:01:08,623
(PAXTON WHIMPERING)

1283
01:01:10,556 --> 01:01:11,827
(BARNES INHALES SHARPLY)

1284
01:01:11,929 --> 01:01:12,924
(PAXTON GASPS)

1285
01:01:15,130 --> 01:01:17,093
(BONES CRACKING)

1286
01:01:24,405 --> 01:01:26,069
What's happening to her?

1287
01:01:26,943 --> 01:01:28,572
(RATTLE)

1288
01:01:28,675 --> 01:01:30,843
<i>(CREEP</i> BY RADIOHEAD PLAYING)

1289
01:01:37,287 --> 01:01:38,218
(MR. REED MOCKINGLY SINGING)

1290
01:01:38,320 --> 01:01:39,522
<i>♪ But I'm a creep ♪</i>

1291
01:01:40,189 --> 01:01:42,353
<i>♪ I'm a weirdo ♪</i>

1292
01:01:42,455 --> 01:01:43,552
(MR. REED LAUGHING)

1293
01:01:43,654 --> 01:01:45,088
BARNES: Mr. Reed?

1294
01:01:48,297 --> 01:01:49,532
BARNES: Where are you?

1295
01:01:49,634 --> 01:01:51,798
- (BARNES BREATHING HEAVILY)
- (MR. REED HUMS ALONG)

1296
01:01:54,900 --> 01:01:57,034
<i>♪ Couldn't look you
in the eye ♪</i>

1297
01:02:00,509 --> 01:02:02,875
<i>♪ You're just like an angel ♪</i>

1298
01:02:05,510 --> 01:02:06,544
(FIRE CRACKLING)

1299
01:02:06,646 --> 01:02:09,211
<i>♪ Your skin makes me cry ♪</i>

1300
01:02:10,119 --> 01:02:12,456
(SCRAPING)

1301
01:02:15,455 --> 01:02:17,461
(GROANING, WHEEZING)

1302
01:02:24,396 --> 01:02:25,661
(SHUSHES)

1303
01:02:25,763 --> 01:02:27,398
(MOUTHING IMPERCEPTIBLY)

1304
01:02:27,500 --> 01:02:29,638
(WHIMPERING SOFTLY)

1305
01:02:31,206 --> 01:02:32,641
(MOUTHING) No.

1306
01:02:33,871 --> 01:02:35,539
(OBJECTS CLANKING IN DISTANCE)

1307
01:02:35,641 --> 01:02:38,009
<i>♪ And I'm a creep ♪</i>

1308
01:02:40,349 --> 01:02:41,811
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1309
01:02:41,913 --> 01:02:44,213
(WOMAN WHISPERING
INDISTINCTLY)

1310
01:02:50,455 --> 01:02:52,628
(PANTING)

1311
01:02:58,901 --> 01:03:01,769
- (MR. REED HUMMING)
<i>- (CREEP</i> CONTINUES PLAYING)

1312
01:03:02,973 --> 01:03:04,532
(PANTING)

1313
01:03:04,635 --> 01:03:05,602
(RATTLING)

1314
01:03:05,704 --> 01:03:07,203
<i>♪ I wanna have control ♪</i>

1315
01:03:10,644 --> 01:03:12,507
<i>♪ I want a perfect body ♪</i>

1316
01:03:12,610 --> 01:03:14,947
(SCRAPING)

1317
01:03:15,848 --> 01:03:17,549
(SCRAPING,
THUDDING BEHIND DOOR)

1318
01:03:17,651 --> 01:03:20,656
<i>♪ I want a perfect soul ♪</i>

1319
01:03:22,259 --> 01:03:24,957
<i>♪ I want you to notice ♪</i>

1320
01:03:27,825 --> 01:03:29,558
<i>♪ When I'm not around ♪</i>

1321
01:03:29,660 --> 01:03:32,030
(LOUD BANGING)

1322
01:03:33,337 --> 01:03:36,298
<i>♪ You're so very special ♪</i>

1323
01:03:39,441 --> 01:03:41,644
<i>♪ But I'm a creep ♪</i>

1324
01:03:45,413 --> 01:03:48,277
<i>♪ I'm a weirdo ♪</i>

1325
01:03:50,488 --> 01:03:53,821
<i>♪ What the hell
am I doin' here? ♪</i>

1326
01:03:56,656 --> 01:03:58,561
<i>♪ I don't belong here ♪</i>

1327
01:03:58,663 --> 01:04:00,223
- (TAPE PLAYER SCREECHES)
<i>- (CREEP</i> STOPS PLAYING)

1328
01:04:02,930 --> 01:04:04,399
MR. REED OVER SPEAKERS:
<i>I had to be sure</i>

1329
01:04:04,501 --> 01:04:06,031
<i>before I introduced you
to her.</i>

1330
01:04:07,064 --> 01:04:09,568
Sure about what?
(BREATH TREMBLING)

1331
01:04:09,670 --> 01:04:11,608
You are now in the presence

1332
01:04:12,508 --> 01:04:14,640
of a living prophet of God.

1333
01:04:14,742 --> 01:04:17,075
(WOMAN WHISPERING
INDISTINCTLY)

1334
01:04:22,717 --> 01:04:24,984
- (WOMAN WHEEZING)
- (BONES CRACKING)

1335
01:04:32,156 --> 01:04:33,562
MR. REED: <i>The reason
I invited you</i>

1336
01:04:33,664 --> 01:04:35,792
<i>into my sanctuary tonight
is because</i>

1337
01:04:35,894 --> 01:04:37,700
<i>I have been shown a miracle.</i>

1338
01:04:38,899 --> 01:04:40,262
<i>I believe
this miracle is proof</i>

1339
01:04:40,364 --> 01:04:43,198
<i>that all known religions
are demonstrably false,</i>

1340
01:04:43,301 --> 01:04:47,842
<i>and only an ancient echo
of something true.</i>

1341
01:04:49,576 --> 01:04:51,272
<i>I need a witness,</i>

1342
01:04:51,375 --> 01:04:55,817
<i>you, to verify
that the miracle is real.</i>

1343
01:04:57,651 --> 01:04:59,854
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

1344
01:05:10,394 --> 01:05:13,302
<i>Now, our family recipe
for blueberry pie is,</i>

1345
01:05:13,404 --> 01:05:14,902
<i>I think, a traditional one.</i>

1346
01:05:15,004 --> 01:05:18,139
The ingredients include
butter, flour, corn starch,

1347
01:05:18,241 --> 01:05:19,571
sugar, lemon,

1348
01:05:19,673 --> 01:05:21,544
blueberries, of course,

1349
01:05:21,647 --> 01:05:24,509
but tonight I've also included
some wolf's bane

1350
01:05:24,611 --> 01:05:25,946
and some belladonna,

1351
01:05:26,979 --> 01:05:30,181
which means that,
in a short while,

1352
01:05:32,020 --> 01:05:35,519
the Prophet will be dead
from consuming the pie.

1353
01:05:35,621 --> 01:05:37,793
(SQUELCHING)

1354
01:05:38,859 --> 01:05:39,889
MR. REED OVER SPEAKERS:
<i>Then,</i>

1355
01:05:39,991 --> 01:05:42,963
<i>you will witness a miracle.</i>

1356
01:05:44,631 --> 01:05:46,802
By the grace of God,

1357
01:05:48,273 --> 01:05:49,673
she will be resurrected.

1358
01:05:50,175 --> 01:05:52,368
(WHEEZING WEAKLY)

1359
01:05:58,042 --> 01:06:00,376
(CONTINUES WHEEZING WEAKLY)

1360
01:06:20,769 --> 01:06:22,739
- (RETCHES)
- (LANTERN CLATTERS)

1361
01:06:27,907 --> 01:06:29,372
Now, feel her pulse, please.

1362
01:06:30,808 --> 01:06:31,979
Both of you.

1363
01:06:33,316 --> 01:06:34,946
(WATER DRIPPING)

1364
01:06:35,048 --> 01:06:36,352
MR. REED OVER SPEAKERS:
<i>I need you</i>

1365
01:06:36,454 --> 01:06:38,854
<i>to feel her pulse right now!</i>

1366
01:06:42,855 --> 01:06:44,254
(PAXTON BREATHING HEAVILY)

1367
01:06:44,356 --> 01:06:45,925
MR. REED OVER SPEAKERS:
<i>Acknowledge, please,</i>

1368
01:06:46,027 --> 01:06:48,056
<i>that her heart has now
stopped pumping.</i>

1369
01:06:48,158 --> 01:06:50,392
<i>Do you know how to do that?</i>

1370
01:06:50,494 --> 01:06:52,197
<i>Index and middle finger
on the side of the neck,</i>

1371
01:06:52,299 --> 01:06:55,332
<i>in the soft, hollow area
just beside the windpipe.</i>

1372
01:06:56,967 --> 01:06:58,336
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1373
01:06:58,438 --> 01:07:01,074
MR. REED: <i>Both of you, please,
lift her head to be sure.</i>

1374
01:07:04,314 --> 01:07:05,980
(SQUELCHING)

1375
01:07:08,451 --> 01:07:10,754
(PAXTON SHUDDERS)

1376
01:07:12,591 --> 01:07:13,554
- (PROPHET GURGLES)
- (PAXTON GASPS)

1377
01:07:13,656 --> 01:07:14,956
PAXTON: She moved! She moved!

1378
01:07:15,058 --> 01:07:17,525
MR. REED: (LAUGHING) <i>That was
just a catalytic spasm.</i>

1379
01:07:17,627 --> 01:07:18,955
PAXTON: (GASPS) She's alive!

1380
01:07:19,058 --> 01:07:20,630
MR. REED: <i>No! No, no. Not yet.</i>

1381
01:07:20,732 --> 01:07:22,292
<i>Chemicals being released
into her body.</i>

1382
01:07:22,394 --> 01:07:24,266
<i>Acknowledge, please,
that there's no pulse.</i>

1383
01:07:24,368 --> 01:07:25,398
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1384
01:07:25,500 --> 01:07:26,501
<i>Acknowledge!</i>

1385
01:07:26,603 --> 01:07:27,633
- No. No pulse.
- No pulse.

1386
01:07:27,735 --> 01:07:28,870
MR. REED: <i>Thank you.</i>

1387
01:07:28,972 --> 01:07:31,236
<i>Acknowledge that she is
no longer breathing.</i>

1388
01:07:33,774 --> 01:07:34,943
<i>Do you feel a breath?</i>

1389
01:07:39,713 --> 01:07:40,847
BARNES: No. No.

1390
01:07:40,949 --> 01:07:41,978
MR. REED: <i>So she's dead.</i>
BARNES: Yes.

1391
01:07:42,081 --> 01:07:43,853
- (WHIMPERS)
- MR. REED: <i>Okay.</i>

1392
01:07:44,453 --> 01:07:45,988
<i>Thank you.</i>

1393
01:07:46,090 --> 01:07:51,256
<i>A moment longer, and you will
witness a resurrection.</i>

1394
01:07:52,389 --> 01:07:54,991
<i>She'll return
and she will tell us</i>

1395
01:07:55,094 --> 01:07:56,932
<i>what she saw in the afterlife.</i>

1396
01:07:59,668 --> 01:08:00,969
Has the Prophet moved?

1397
01:08:01,670 --> 01:08:03,203
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1398
01:08:03,305 --> 01:08:04,804
No.

1399
01:08:04,906 --> 01:08:05,868
MR. REED OVER SPEAKERS:
<i>Hello?</i>

1400
01:08:05,970 --> 01:08:07,573
- No. No.
- Mmm-mmm.

1401
01:08:07,675 --> 01:08:08,777
(BARNES WHIMPERS)

1402
01:08:08,880 --> 01:08:11,474
MR. REED: <i>All right.
Just</i> un momentino.

1403
01:08:16,553 --> 01:08:17,953
<i>Only a moment longer.</i>

1404
01:08:19,523 --> 01:08:21,451
- (BELL RINGING)
- (GASPS)

1405
01:08:23,320 --> 01:08:24,927
(BREATHING RAPIDLY)
The Elders?

1406
01:08:27,364 --> 01:08:29,393
(DOORBELL RINGS)

1407
01:08:31,831 --> 01:08:33,697
(FOOTSTEPS ECHOING)

1408
01:08:33,799 --> 01:08:36,037
(DOOR LOCKS)

1409
01:08:40,173 --> 01:08:42,340
- (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)
- (BOTH PANTING)

1410
01:08:44,842 --> 01:08:46,878
(PANTING)

1411
01:08:46,980 --> 01:08:48,982
- We scream.
- We scream.

1412
01:08:49,084 --> 01:08:51,448
BARNES: But not until
he answers the door.

1413
01:08:57,328 --> 01:08:59,095
(KNOCKING)

1414
01:08:59,964 --> 01:09:01,497
PAXTON: He's coming back.
BARNES: Scream! Scream!

1415
01:09:01,599 --> 01:09:03,497
(PAXTON AND BARNES SCREAMING)

1416
01:09:03,599 --> 01:09:04,393
(DOOR CREAKING)

1417
01:09:04,495 --> 01:09:06,936
- (DOOR SHUTS)
- (BOTH CONTINUE SCREAMING)

1418
01:09:07,536 --> 01:09:08,564
(LIGHTS CLICK)

1419
01:09:12,443 --> 01:09:13,602
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1420
01:09:15,412 --> 01:09:16,739
(KNOCKING)

1421
01:09:16,841 --> 01:09:18,178
Coming!

1422
01:09:19,349 --> 01:09:21,346
(TICKING)

1423
01:09:26,687 --> 01:09:27,655
Ah! Sorry!

1424
01:09:27,757 --> 01:09:28,856
I was at the back. (CHUCKLES)

1425
01:09:28,958 --> 01:09:30,760
- No, I'm sorry to bother you.
- No.

1426
01:09:30,862 --> 01:09:32,122
I'm just in the neighborhood
looking for

1427
01:09:32,224 --> 01:09:34,228
two young ladies
from my church.

1428
01:09:34,330 --> 01:09:35,294
Oh.

1429
01:09:36,193 --> 01:09:37,398
Is everything all right?

1430
01:09:37,500 --> 01:09:39,463
(BOTH SCREAMING)

1431
01:09:40,701 --> 01:09:42,030
(BOTH PANTING)

1432
01:09:42,132 --> 01:09:43,940
They can't hear us.

1433
01:09:44,908 --> 01:09:46,104
MAN: <i>I'm sure
everything's fine,</i>

1434
01:09:46,206 --> 01:09:47,408
<i>I was just wondering
if they...</i>

1435
01:09:47,510 --> 01:09:48,475
(WIND BLOWING)

1436
01:09:48,577 --> 01:09:49,544
...stopped by.

1437
01:09:49,646 --> 01:09:50,705
No. I'm sorry to say,

1438
01:09:50,807 --> 01:09:54,677
you are the first house caller
I've had all day, so.

1439
01:09:55,313 --> 01:09:57,613
- Did you see this?
- It's locked.

1440
01:10:01,755 --> 01:10:02,719
BARNES: Help.

1441
01:10:02,821 --> 01:10:04,085
Help.

1442
01:10:04,187 --> 01:10:06,790
We can pull the rug.

1443
01:10:06,892 --> 01:10:07,824
The matches.

1444
01:10:07,926 --> 01:10:09,766
We start a fire,

1445
01:10:09,868 --> 01:10:11,028
smoke out the speaking pipe
to make sure

1446
01:10:11,130 --> 01:10:12,831
the Elder knows we're here.

1447
01:10:12,933 --> 01:10:15,838
Okay. But you did ask

1448
01:10:15,941 --> 01:10:18,202
for more information
on the church, correct?

1449
01:10:18,304 --> 01:10:20,074
Uh, this...
this is the which church?

1450
01:10:20,176 --> 01:10:21,575
The Church of Jesus Christ
of Latter-day Saints.

1451
01:10:21,677 --> 01:10:23,972
Yes, yes, yes, yes.

1452
01:10:24,074 --> 01:10:26,449
(WIND BLOWING)

1453
01:10:26,551 --> 01:10:27,978
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1454
01:10:28,080 --> 01:10:30,514
BARNES: Pull. Careful.

1455
01:10:35,926 --> 01:10:37,519
Is there some other way
I can help?

1456
01:10:37,621 --> 01:10:39,588
Do you want to use my phone,
call the police?

1457
01:10:39,690 --> 01:10:41,290
- I could get my coat...
- No, no. That's fine.

1458
01:10:41,392 --> 01:10:42,491
...and come help you
look around.

1459
01:10:42,594 --> 01:10:44,165
No, no, no, no, no.
I'm sure they're not far.

1460
01:10:44,900 --> 01:10:46,001
Uh, thank you for your time.

1461
01:10:46,103 --> 01:10:48,602
All right, well, good luck.
Yeah, I mean that.

1462
01:10:48,704 --> 01:10:50,039
- Okay.
- Uh-huh.

1463
01:10:50,771 --> 01:10:52,239
(WIND BLOWING)

1464
01:10:53,842 --> 01:10:56,045
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1465
01:11:05,890 --> 01:11:08,156
- (MUSIC STOPS PLAYING)
- (DOOR CREAKS)

1466
01:11:13,794 --> 01:11:14,858
(CREAKING)

1467
01:11:14,960 --> 01:11:16,796
(FOOTSTEPS)

1468
01:11:16,898 --> 01:11:18,465
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1469
01:11:18,567 --> 01:11:19,596
(CLICKS)

1470
01:11:21,165 --> 01:11:23,369
(WATER POURING)

1471
01:11:24,408 --> 01:11:25,199
(THUD)

1472
01:11:25,301 --> 01:11:26,870
(FURNITURE DRAGGING)

1473
01:11:26,972 --> 01:11:28,737
(FOOTSTEPS)

1474
01:11:36,949 --> 01:11:38,417
(CLICKING)

1475
01:11:39,688 --> 01:11:41,052
(SCRAPING)

1476
01:11:41,155 --> 01:11:43,488
- (FLOOR CREAKING)
- (FOOTSTEPS)

1477
01:11:53,538 --> 01:11:54,796
(MR. REED COUGHS)

1478
01:11:55,871 --> 01:11:57,502
(MR. REED CLEARS THROAT)

1479
01:11:59,169 --> 01:12:01,077
(OBJECT DRAGS)

1480
01:12:06,749 --> 01:12:07,744
(TENSE MUSIC BUILDS)

1481
01:12:07,846 --> 01:12:09,283
No.

1482
01:12:15,724 --> 01:12:17,687
(CLICKING)

1483
01:12:18,727 --> 01:12:20,459
(FOOTSTEPS)

1484
01:12:21,193 --> 01:12:23,396
(BARNES BREATHING HEAVILY)

1485
01:12:25,031 --> 01:12:26,300
(BARNES GRUNTS)

1486
01:12:28,398 --> 01:12:29,464
- (THUD)
- (DOOR CREAKS)

1487
01:12:29,566 --> 01:12:31,204
PAXTON: (WHISPERING)
He's coming!

1488
01:12:31,306 --> 01:12:33,538
- (FOOTSTEPS)
- (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1489
01:12:34,039 --> 01:12:35,743
(DOORBELL RINGS)

1490
01:12:35,845 --> 01:12:37,839
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1491
01:12:41,519 --> 01:12:42,613
(RATTLING)

1492
01:12:43,380 --> 01:12:46,117
Yeah? Yeah? Any luck?

1493
01:12:46,219 --> 01:12:48,289
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1494
01:12:54,432 --> 01:12:55,428
(GASPS)

1495
01:12:56,897 --> 01:12:58,334
She moved.

1496
01:12:59,036 --> 01:13:00,730
- What do you mean?
- When we were gone.

1497
01:13:04,172 --> 01:13:06,004
No,
you're remembering it wrong.

1498
01:13:06,106 --> 01:13:07,104
She hasn't moved at all.

1499
01:13:07,206 --> 01:13:08,173
Her head is different.

1500
01:13:08,275 --> 01:13:10,606
- That's where she was!
- It's not!

1501
01:13:10,709 --> 01:13:13,276
Sister, that's not
how I remember it. Please!

1502
01:13:13,378 --> 01:13:15,712
Please, just come on! Help!

1503
01:13:16,412 --> 01:13:18,253
Hold the sleeve up.

1504
01:13:20,884 --> 01:13:25,557
I'd be remiss if I didn't
ask you one question.

1505
01:13:26,258 --> 01:13:28,362
(DRAMATIC MUSIC BUILDS)

1506
01:13:29,866 --> 01:13:30,833
(MUSIC STOPS PLAYING)

1507
01:13:30,935 --> 01:13:33,367
Have you received
this booklet?

1508
01:13:34,671 --> 01:13:36,035
I have not,

1509
01:13:36,137 --> 01:13:38,740
but I will give it a look-see.

1510
01:13:38,842 --> 01:13:40,873
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1511
01:13:40,975 --> 01:13:41,874
PAXTON: Try another.

1512
01:13:41,976 --> 01:13:43,271
BARNES: I know.

1513
01:13:43,373 --> 01:13:45,676
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1514
01:13:48,717 --> 01:13:50,145
Focus.

1515
01:13:50,247 --> 01:13:51,814
(WIND BLOWING)

1516
01:13:53,822 --> 01:13:55,719
(RATTLING)

1517
01:13:56,153 --> 01:13:57,153
Faster.

1518
01:13:57,255 --> 01:13:58,854
(MATCH IGNITES)

1519
01:13:59,730 --> 01:14:00,691
(BARNES WHIMPERS)

1520
01:14:01,865 --> 01:14:03,925
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC BUILDS)

1521
01:14:12,939 --> 01:14:14,177
(GASPS)

1522
01:14:15,075 --> 01:14:16,044
(BARNES GRUNTS)

1523
01:14:16,146 --> 01:14:17,906
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING)

1524
01:14:24,448 --> 01:14:25,686
(MUSIC STOPS PLAYING)

1525
01:14:25,788 --> 01:14:27,723
(WIND GUSTING)

1526
01:14:27,825 --> 01:14:28,818
(MATCH SCRAPING ON WALL)

1527
01:14:31,663 --> 01:14:32,893
(BARNES WHIMPERS)

1528
01:14:32,995 --> 01:14:35,731
(BARNES BREATHING HEAVILY)

1529
01:14:35,833 --> 01:14:37,893
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

1530
01:14:42,839 --> 01:14:43,804
(MATCH IGNITES)

1531
01:14:43,906 --> 01:14:45,841
- (SCREAMS)
- (GASPS)

1532
01:14:45,943 --> 01:14:48,041
- (BOTH GASPING)
- (WHEEZES)

1533
01:14:48,143 --> 01:14:51,313
- (RETCHES)
- (BOTH GASPING)

1534
01:14:53,243 --> 01:14:54,417
(RETCHES)

1535
01:14:54,519 --> 01:14:55,717
(COUGHS)

1536
01:14:55,819 --> 01:14:57,649
(PROPHET WHEEZES)

1537
01:14:59,351 --> 01:15:01,687
PROPHET: Conductor...

1538
01:15:02,089 --> 01:15:05,954
says... my... name.

1539
01:15:06,697 --> 01:15:09,793
White... clouds.

1540
01:15:10,327 --> 01:15:13,196
Not... Heaven.

1541
01:15:13,298 --> 01:15:16,899
They... unplug...

1542
01:15:17,608 --> 01:15:19,572
my brain.

1543
01:15:20,809 --> 01:15:23,246
It is...

1544
01:15:24,714 --> 01:15:25,710
not...

1545
01:15:26,210 --> 01:15:27,849
real.

1546
01:15:27,951 --> 01:15:28,951
(INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1547
01:15:29,053 --> 01:15:31,284
MR. REED:
And, thank you, Prophet.

1548
01:15:31,386 --> 01:15:32,985
We are very grateful
for your passage

1549
01:15:33,087 --> 01:15:34,589
to the other side.

1550
01:15:34,692 --> 01:15:35,787
(WHEEZING)

1551
01:15:35,889 --> 01:15:39,788
Your prophecy will be recorded
into our liturgical texts.

1552
01:15:39,890 --> 01:15:43,194
Come. You must be exhausted.
Take my arm.

1553
01:15:43,296 --> 01:15:45,301
(UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING)

1554
01:15:47,938 --> 01:15:49,899
(BARNES BREATHING HEAVILY)

1555
01:15:52,569 --> 01:15:53,741
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

1556
01:15:53,843 --> 01:15:55,875
(INAUDIBLE)

1557
01:15:55,977 --> 01:15:57,973
(DOOR UNLOCKS)

1558
01:15:58,749 --> 01:15:59,843
(MATCH SCRAPING)

1559
01:16:01,819 --> 01:16:02,784
(PROPHET WHIMPERS)

1560
01:16:02,886 --> 01:16:03,880
(DOOR CREAKS, SHUTS)

1561
01:16:08,385 --> 01:16:09,622
Well, now.

1562
01:16:11,428 --> 01:16:13,227
You see, this is rather
interesting because...

1563
01:16:13,329 --> 01:16:15,493
- (OBJECT CLANKS)
- (MR. REED CHUCKLES)

1564
01:16:15,595 --> 01:16:19,731
I know that one of you
has been lying

1565
01:16:21,205 --> 01:16:23,533
since you first got here.
(CHUCKLING)

1566
01:16:23,635 --> 01:16:25,767
And do you know
how I know that?

1567
01:16:25,869 --> 01:16:27,468
Excuse me, can I...
can I take that?

1568
01:16:27,570 --> 01:16:29,639
I know from the way

1569
01:16:29,741 --> 01:16:33,845
that the fire reacts
to each of you.

1570
01:16:33,947 --> 01:16:34,911
A.

1571
01:16:36,686 --> 01:16:37,946
B.

1572
01:16:38,048 --> 01:16:40,289
Yeah. One of you has
a very, very... (CHUCKLING)

1573
01:16:40,391 --> 01:16:44,292
...very big secret,
but we will know more soon.

1574
01:16:44,394 --> 01:16:46,690
There will be
before you saw a woman die

1575
01:16:46,793 --> 01:16:49,857
and come back to life,
and there will be after.

1576
01:16:49,959 --> 01:16:52,026
(BLOWS) Books will be written
about it.

1577
01:16:52,128 --> 01:16:55,503
So choose your words
very carefully when I ask,

1578
01:16:56,171 --> 01:16:57,340
what did you witness?

1579
01:16:59,406 --> 01:17:00,673
Tell me. Tell me what you saw.

1580
01:17:01,471 --> 01:17:02,943
How did she...

1581
01:17:03,045 --> 01:17:03,972
I don't know...

1582
01:17:04,074 --> 01:17:06,014
And if you didn't
see something transcendental,

1583
01:17:06,116 --> 01:17:07,177
you absolutely must tell me.

1584
01:17:07,279 --> 01:17:08,850
I don't know.

1585
01:17:08,952 --> 01:17:09,812
'Cause if I'm wrong,

1586
01:17:09,914 --> 01:17:11,354
I need to hear it.
That's why you're here.

1587
01:17:11,456 --> 01:17:12,914
It's a contrived experiment.
We are your prisoners!

1588
01:17:13,017 --> 01:17:14,622
- It doesn't make sense...
- MR. REED: Oh, pooh!

1589
01:17:14,724 --> 01:17:15,785
- We're all prisoners together.
- ...for us to have an opinion!

1590
01:17:15,887 --> 01:17:16,884
You must know by now
that any of us can leave

1591
01:17:16,986 --> 01:17:19,290
whenever we want,
but why would we want,

1592
01:17:19,392 --> 01:17:20,521
after what we've seen?

1593
01:17:20,623 --> 01:17:23,029
I saw it. I saw it.

1594
01:17:23,131 --> 01:17:24,562
I heard her describe

1595
01:17:24,664 --> 01:17:26,297
what she experienced
on the other side.

1596
01:17:26,399 --> 01:17:28,300
Great! What did you hear?

1597
01:17:28,403 --> 01:17:31,568
She said
there was a conductor.

1598
01:17:31,670 --> 01:17:34,374
- Yes. Yeah.
- Did she mean angel?

1599
01:17:34,476 --> 01:17:36,871
She had a feeling
of disassociation,

1600
01:17:36,973 --> 01:17:39,714
a feeling that something
wasn't real.

1601
01:17:39,817 --> 01:17:40,845
That's it.

1602
01:17:41,852 --> 01:17:42,814
So now you know.

1603
01:17:44,382 --> 01:17:45,381
Now, we know?

1604
01:17:45,483 --> 01:17:46,785
Yeah, now, you know.

1605
01:17:48,022 --> 01:17:48,985
Know?

1606
01:17:50,224 --> 01:17:51,592
I can show you God.

1607
01:17:53,030 --> 01:17:55,693
If you're willing to die.

1608
01:17:55,796 --> 01:17:58,662
It... it can be painless.
It can be temporary.

1609
01:17:58,764 --> 01:18:00,898
Like the Prophet,
you can be brought back.

1610
01:18:01,966 --> 01:18:03,571
It doesn't have
to be frightening at all.

1611
01:18:03,673 --> 01:18:05,106
I'll tell you... I'll tell you
what's frightening.

1612
01:18:05,208 --> 01:18:06,639
Not knowing is frightening!

1613
01:18:06,741 --> 01:18:08,272
Where do we come from?
What are we doing here?

1614
01:18:08,374 --> 01:18:09,610
What's our purpose?

1615
01:18:09,712 --> 01:18:12,511
The terror of those questions
is why religions exist.

1616
01:18:12,613 --> 01:18:14,382
I can answer
those questions for you.

1617
01:18:14,485 --> 01:18:17,684
I can give you a comfort
no religion in the world

1618
01:18:18,451 --> 01:18:19,752
is capable of giving you.

1619
01:18:21,784 --> 01:18:23,690
It all makes sense now.

1620
01:18:25,824 --> 01:18:27,925
I've been asking myself
all night,

1621
01:18:28,894 --> 01:18:31,459
how is he gonna
make killing us our idea?

1622
01:18:31,561 --> 01:18:32,732
(MR. REED SIGHS)

1623
01:18:34,668 --> 01:18:36,036
Sister Barnes,
you're in a muddle.

1624
01:18:36,138 --> 01:18:36,898
I know. I can't tell

1625
01:18:37,000 --> 01:18:38,969
if you're playing chess
or checkers.

1626
01:18:39,502 --> 01:18:41,142
Monopoly!

1627
01:18:41,244 --> 01:18:42,275
Come on, it was right there.

1628
01:18:42,377 --> 01:18:44,243
You didn't show us a miracle.

1629
01:18:44,345 --> 01:18:45,976
Okay, what did I show you?

1630
01:18:46,578 --> 01:18:48,416
That wasn't a miracle.

1631
01:18:48,518 --> 01:18:50,249
MR. REED: So you say.
What did I show you?

1632
01:18:50,351 --> 01:18:52,349
That was not a miracle!

1633
01:18:52,451 --> 01:18:53,819
What did I show you?

1634
01:18:55,554 --> 01:18:58,087
It was a magic trick.

1635
01:19:00,031 --> 01:19:01,359
MR. REED: A magic trick?

1636
01:19:01,461 --> 01:19:03,664
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1637
01:19:06,702 --> 01:19:09,700
You wanna know why
we don't talk about Taco Bell?

1638
01:19:09,802 --> 01:19:11,540
It killed me
when I was four years old.

1639
01:19:11,642 --> 01:19:14,738
Fifty people were hospitalized
from an E. coli outbreak.

1640
01:19:14,840 --> 01:19:16,705
The kids at school
called me Taco Hell

1641
01:19:16,807 --> 01:19:18,280
'cause I was clinically dead

1642
01:19:18,382 --> 01:19:20,648
while doctors operated
on my kidneys.

1643
01:19:23,085 --> 01:19:24,815
When I was dead,

1644
01:19:24,917 --> 01:19:28,788
I saw exactly
what your prophet described.

1645
01:19:29,522 --> 01:19:31,120
A blinding white light,

1646
01:19:31,222 --> 01:19:34,760
clouds, but not Heaven,
a sense of wanting to return,

1647
01:19:34,862 --> 01:19:37,533
a feeling that my state
of reality wasn't real.

1648
01:19:39,532 --> 01:19:41,130
That wasn't a prophecy.

1649
01:19:41,999 --> 01:19:45,372
That was a near-death
experience.

1650
01:19:45,474 --> 01:19:46,770
When the oxygen
leaves your brain

1651
01:19:46,872 --> 01:19:49,441
or your heart stops pumping,
your mind

1652
01:19:49,543 --> 01:19:51,313
creates unbelievable things.

1653
01:19:51,415 --> 01:19:54,814
I think you've been
keeping this woman

1654
01:19:54,916 --> 01:19:56,944
on the edge of death
in order to ask her questions

1655
01:19:57,046 --> 01:19:59,453
about meaningless
hallucinations

1656
01:19:59,555 --> 01:20:01,785
so that you can substantiate
your idea

1657
01:20:01,887 --> 01:20:05,187
of what the one,
true religion really is.

1658
01:20:06,394 --> 01:20:08,230
MR. REED: Did you know...

1659
01:20:08,332 --> 01:20:09,296
that when you remember
something,

1660
01:20:09,398 --> 01:20:10,465
you're really only remembering

1661
01:20:10,567 --> 01:20:12,227
the last time you remembered
that experience?

1662
01:20:14,032 --> 01:20:15,329
You're not actually
recalling the event.

1663
01:20:15,431 --> 01:20:19,668
So your memory of dying
at Taco Bell... (CHUCKLING)

1664
01:20:19,770 --> 01:20:20,803
...isn't really of dying,

1665
01:20:20,905 --> 01:20:22,741
it's of the memory
of the memory

1666
01:20:22,844 --> 01:20:24,412
of the memory
of the memory of the memory...

1667
01:20:24,514 --> 01:20:27,746
stop me... (CHUCKLES)
...of that event.

1668
01:20:27,848 --> 01:20:29,847
So you're remembering
a false correlation

1669
01:20:29,949 --> 01:20:31,617
with the experience
you've just witnessed.

1670
01:20:31,719 --> 01:20:35,723
But this,
this is happening right now!

1671
01:20:35,825 --> 01:20:38,855
That's why I think,
Sister Barnes, Sister Paxton,

1672
01:20:38,957 --> 01:20:40,791
that you really need
to pay attention

1673
01:20:40,893 --> 01:20:42,431
because I promise you...
(CHUCKLING)

1674
01:20:42,533 --> 01:20:44,292
...we're not talking
about a magic trick.

1675
01:20:45,565 --> 01:20:47,603
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1676
01:20:50,599 --> 01:20:51,670
No,

1677
01:20:51,772 --> 01:20:54,343
we're talking
about magic underwear...

1678
01:20:54,445 --> 01:20:55,908
- (SLASHING)
- (MUSIC STOPS PLAYING)

1679
01:21:01,581 --> 01:21:02,849
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1680
01:21:06,685 --> 01:21:08,855
(INAUDIBLE SCREAMING)

1681
01:21:16,694 --> 01:21:18,931
(IMPERCEPTIBLE)

1682
01:21:23,735 --> 01:21:25,971
(INAUDIBLE SCREAMING)

1683
01:21:39,454 --> 01:21:41,451
(SCREAMING) Help me! Help!

1684
01:21:41,553 --> 01:21:43,351
(WIND GUSTING)

1685
01:21:47,558 --> 01:21:49,797
(SOBS)

1686
01:21:51,234 --> 01:21:52,393
(INHALES SHARPLY)

1687
01:21:54,499 --> 01:21:55,803
(SIGHS)

1688
01:21:58,439 --> 01:21:59,605
(EXHALES SHAKILY)

1689
01:21:59,707 --> 01:22:01,204
MR. REED:
She'll come back to us!

1690
01:22:02,343 --> 01:22:03,646
I promise!

1691
01:22:05,977 --> 01:22:08,116
Sister Paxton,
do not be scared!

1692
01:22:08,218 --> 01:22:09,311
She will rise again.

1693
01:22:10,087 --> 01:22:11,315
Challenge him.

1694
01:22:11,417 --> 01:22:12,380
Debate.

1695
01:22:13,090 --> 01:22:14,151
Challenge him.

1696
01:22:15,291 --> 01:22:17,055
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1697
01:22:20,394 --> 01:22:22,023
(FOOTSTEPS)

1698
01:22:22,125 --> 01:22:24,260
MR. REED: Come on, now,
Sister B.

1699
01:22:25,663 --> 01:22:27,436
Wakey-wakey!

1700
01:22:27,538 --> 01:22:28,899
- (WATER DRIPPING)
- Whoa, whoa, whoa,

1701
01:22:29,001 --> 01:22:30,604
whoa, whoa, whoa!
No, that's not it.

1702
01:22:30,706 --> 01:22:33,407
That's not it.
That's a... a mucky pup.

1703
01:22:33,509 --> 01:22:34,677
Let's have that.
(CHUCKLES)

1704
01:22:37,941 --> 01:22:39,910
Moments. It'll be moments.

1705
01:22:40,012 --> 01:22:41,343
Let's have one
of your drum rolls, yeah?

1706
01:22:44,219 --> 01:22:45,182
Whoop!

1707
01:22:48,555 --> 01:22:50,693
Hey! (SNIFFLES)

1708
01:22:53,857 --> 01:22:55,361
I'm very sorry.

1709
01:22:55,463 --> 01:22:57,096
Something is wrong.

1710
01:22:57,565 --> 01:22:59,167
(UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING)

1711
01:22:59,269 --> 01:23:00,362
I'm now worried...

1712
01:23:02,404 --> 01:23:03,501
that she's not...

1713
01:23:03,603 --> 01:23:04,602
(BOX CUTTER OPENS)

1714
01:23:04,704 --> 01:23:05,939
...coming back to us.

1715
01:23:08,672 --> 01:23:09,705
Yeah.

1716
01:23:09,807 --> 01:23:11,276
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1717
01:23:11,378 --> 01:23:12,545
Oh, yeah.

1718
01:23:12,648 --> 01:23:14,783
- (SOBS)
- MR. REED: Oh, yeah.

1719
01:23:18,219 --> 01:23:19,183
Yep.

1720
01:23:20,089 --> 01:23:21,053
Yep.

1721
01:23:21,619 --> 01:23:22,750
Yeah.

1722
01:23:22,852 --> 01:23:24,355
There it is.

1723
01:23:24,457 --> 01:23:25,687
(GRUNTS)

1724
01:23:25,789 --> 01:23:26,820
No, it isn't.

1725
01:23:26,922 --> 01:23:28,526
That was a vein.

1726
01:23:28,628 --> 01:23:29,724
(MR. REED GRUNTS)

1727
01:23:29,826 --> 01:23:31,530
(SQUELCHING)

1728
01:23:31,632 --> 01:23:34,367
A-ha! (CHUCKLES) A-ha.

1729
01:23:34,469 --> 01:23:36,365
(TENSE MUSIC BUILDS)

1730
01:23:37,669 --> 01:23:38,606
The implant.

1731
01:23:38,708 --> 01:23:41,238
This is why she can't
come back to us.

1732
01:23:42,311 --> 01:23:43,306
Take a look!

1733
01:23:44,248 --> 01:23:45,540
I'm very sorry.

1734
01:23:46,176 --> 01:23:49,378
But Sister Barnes,
she's a program.

1735
01:23:51,981 --> 01:23:53,916
She's not real.

1736
01:23:54,018 --> 01:23:55,758
Do you know what gave it away?

1737
01:23:56,226 --> 01:23:57,087
The candles.

1738
01:23:57,189 --> 01:23:59,824
What are you saying?
I don't understand.

1739
01:23:59,926 --> 01:24:01,797
No, no, I know.
I know. I know.

1740
01:24:02,430 --> 01:24:03,392
How could you?

1741
01:24:05,631 --> 01:24:07,396
(SHUDDERS)

1742
01:24:08,735 --> 01:24:11,070
Can you explain it to me?

1743
01:24:13,872 --> 01:24:16,808
Are you, Sister Paxton,

1744
01:24:16,910 --> 01:24:19,809
familiar with
the Daoist concept

1745
01:24:19,911 --> 01:24:21,712
of "The Butterfly Dream"?

1746
01:24:21,814 --> 01:24:23,412
PAXTON: A butterfly...

1747
01:24:23,514 --> 01:24:26,818
A butterfly flaps its wings
and causes a typhoon?

1748
01:24:26,920 --> 01:24:28,184
That is
"The Butterfly Effect."

1749
01:24:28,286 --> 01:24:30,785
Common mistake. No.
"The Butterfly Dream"...

1750
01:24:30,887 --> 01:24:32,188
(CLATTERING)

1751
01:24:32,290 --> 01:24:34,190
...concerns an ancient
Chinese philosopher

1752
01:24:34,292 --> 01:24:35,928
who asked himself
the following question.

1753
01:24:36,030 --> 01:24:38,225
- (OBJECT CLATTERS)
- "Was I a man dreaming

1754
01:24:38,327 --> 01:24:40,068
"I'm a butterfly,
or am I now..."

1755
01:24:40,170 --> 01:24:40,932
(THUD)

1756
01:24:41,034 --> 01:24:44,239
"...a butterfly dreaming
that I am a man?"

1757
01:24:44,341 --> 01:24:45,605
Come and sit down.

1758
01:24:45,708 --> 01:24:47,273
Come on.
(CLICKS TONGUE) Here.

1759
01:24:47,375 --> 01:24:48,371
(SIGHS)

1760
01:24:50,974 --> 01:24:53,046
(SCRAPING ON TABLE)

1761
01:24:56,253 --> 01:24:57,248
This is us.

1762
01:24:57,916 --> 01:24:59,715
You and me alone together.

1763
01:24:59,817 --> 01:25:01,021
That was Barnes.

1764
01:25:01,621 --> 01:25:02,825
Bye-bye, Barnes.

1765
01:25:03,694 --> 01:25:06,860
I have come
to a dark realization

1766
01:25:06,962 --> 01:25:10,129
that we exist inside
a simulation so advanced

1767
01:25:10,231 --> 01:25:13,000
that we cannot tell the
difference between real life

1768
01:25:13,965 --> 01:25:15,200
and artificial dream.

1769
01:25:15,302 --> 01:25:20,139
You heard the Prophet.
She said, "It is not real."

1770
01:25:20,241 --> 01:25:23,074
You see, fire dynamics
are very difficult to render.

1771
01:25:23,176 --> 01:25:25,779
I've noticed this anomaly
in its behavior

1772
01:25:25,881 --> 01:25:27,976
when it interacts
with simulated NPCs,

1773
01:25:28,078 --> 01:25:31,083
like poor old Sister B.

1774
01:25:31,185 --> 01:25:34,822
She couldn't come back to us,
but when you die,

1775
01:25:34,925 --> 01:25:39,793
finger, please,
you will pass through death

1776
01:25:39,895 --> 01:25:41,990
- and wake up...
- (BOX CUTTER RATTLES)

1777
01:25:42,092 --> 01:25:43,493
...into the real world.

1778
01:25:43,895 --> 01:25:45,366
What do you think?

1779
01:25:45,468 --> 01:25:46,869
Yes, no, maybe?

1780
01:25:48,337 --> 01:25:49,399
Um...

1781
01:25:52,309 --> 01:25:53,876
That's a theory.

1782
01:25:55,339 --> 01:25:57,110
Well yeah,
you're very welcome to...

1783
01:25:58,210 --> 01:25:59,915
to challenge my premise.
I love that.

1784
01:26:01,949 --> 01:26:03,350
- (BOX CUTTER CLOSES)
- Go for it.

1785
01:26:03,452 --> 01:26:05,283
(SNIFFLING)

1786
01:26:08,121 --> 01:26:11,256
I don't think
this is a microchip.

1787
01:26:11,988 --> 01:26:12,956
MR. REED: Oh?

1788
01:26:13,058 --> 01:26:16,030
I think it's a contraceptive.

1789
01:26:17,931 --> 01:26:21,068
A... a birth control implant.

1790
01:26:22,601 --> 01:26:23,598
Huh.

1791
01:26:25,135 --> 01:26:27,402
Tell me, have you ever met

1792
01:26:27,505 --> 01:26:30,176
a Mormon missionary
who was on birth control?

1793
01:26:31,982 --> 01:26:36,949
Did "Sister Barnes" say
she was on birth control?

1794
01:26:37,051 --> 01:26:38,552
PAXTON: Our church
would've made her

1795
01:26:38,654 --> 01:26:40,249
feel ashamed about it,

1796
01:26:40,351 --> 01:26:42,089
and she would've been
too embarrassed.

1797
01:26:43,088 --> 01:26:44,893
- Simulation theory is...
- Ah!

1798
01:26:44,995 --> 01:26:47,688
"Hypothesis," please.
Sorry, it doesn't matter.

1799
01:26:48,664 --> 01:26:51,092
Simulation hypothesis

1800
01:26:51,194 --> 01:26:54,134
is not testable, is it?

1801
01:26:55,401 --> 01:26:58,773
No, it's a matter of belief,
like any religion.

1802
01:26:58,875 --> 01:27:01,138
You either believe it,
green door,

1803
01:27:01,240 --> 01:27:03,077
or you don't believe it,
purple door.

1804
01:27:04,108 --> 01:27:06,674
With all due respect,

1805
01:27:07,910 --> 01:27:09,083
I...

1806
01:27:09,684 --> 01:27:11,549
I don't believe it.

1807
01:27:12,319 --> 01:27:16,187
I'm not smart enough
to say why, I just don't.

1808
01:27:16,290 --> 01:27:18,587
Do you believe the miracle
that I showed you?

1809
01:27:19,396 --> 01:27:20,155
PAXTON: Yes.

1810
01:27:20,257 --> 01:27:22,063
- Yeah?
- PAXTON: At first.

1811
01:27:23,762 --> 01:27:25,062
But now?

1812
01:27:25,164 --> 01:27:27,634
I think something
happened tonight

1813
01:27:27,736 --> 01:27:29,771
that you didn't expect.

1814
01:27:29,873 --> 01:27:31,466
It feels like
you're improvising,

1815
01:27:31,569 --> 01:27:34,071
trying to convince me
of a simulation theory

1816
01:27:34,173 --> 01:27:36,308
that's not sticking.
Am I right?

1817
01:27:39,214 --> 01:27:42,484
Uh, (CHUCKLES) are you
asking me if you're right

1818
01:27:42,586 --> 01:27:43,545
that I am improvising

1819
01:27:43,647 --> 01:27:47,014
or you're right
that the simulation narrative

1820
01:27:47,116 --> 01:27:48,051
is not sticking?

1821
01:27:48,154 --> 01:27:50,586
- Yes.
- (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1822
01:27:53,397 --> 01:27:54,628
High-five.

1823
01:27:54,730 --> 01:27:56,724
(GRUNTS SOFTLY, CHUCKLES)

1824
01:27:57,968 --> 01:27:59,429
So, in fact,
you agree with your friend.

1825
01:27:59,531 --> 01:28:01,968
You think that the Prophet
was just hallucinating

1826
01:28:02,070 --> 01:28:04,204
a meaningless,
near-death experience.

1827
01:28:04,802 --> 01:28:05,932
No.

1828
01:28:06,568 --> 01:28:08,707
I think you switched
the bodies.

1829
01:28:08,809 --> 01:28:10,911
(MUSIC FADES OUT)

1830
01:28:11,013 --> 01:28:13,345
I just haven't
figured out how yet.

1831
01:28:15,144 --> 01:28:16,348
I switched...

1832
01:28:16,981 --> 01:28:18,251
the bodies?

1833
01:28:20,017 --> 01:28:21,254
(FIRE CRACKLING)

1834
01:28:23,619 --> 01:28:26,488
The doorbell rang
when the Elder got here.

1835
01:28:26,590 --> 01:28:29,524
- (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)
- (DOORBELL RINGING)

1836
01:28:29,626 --> 01:28:31,526
<i>Which drew our attention
to the stairs.</i>

1837
01:28:31,628 --> 01:28:34,234
<i>You would have been
prepared for that.</i>

1838
01:28:36,905 --> 01:28:38,206
When we came back downstairs,

1839
01:28:38,308 --> 01:28:41,938
I noticed the woman wasn't in
the same position as before.

1840
01:28:42,040 --> 01:28:43,810
It was similar...

1841
01:28:43,913 --> 01:28:44,844
PAXTON: <i>Her head is different.</i>

1842
01:28:44,947 --> 01:28:48,116
<i>But it was not the exact same.</i>

1843
01:28:48,218 --> 01:28:51,784
<i>I think another woman
who looked exactly like her</i>

1844
01:28:51,886 --> 01:28:53,053
<i>came into the basement</i>

1845
01:28:53,155 --> 01:28:55,355
<i>through a hidden door
or something,</i>

1846
01:28:55,457 --> 01:28:58,854
disposed of her body and then
took her place at the table.

1847
01:28:58,956 --> 01:28:59,993
I see.

1848
01:29:00,095 --> 01:29:02,996
And then,
once we got back downstairs,

1849
01:29:03,098 --> 01:29:07,262
<i>she read off
a scripted prophecy</i>

1850
01:29:07,364 --> 01:29:09,467
<i>that you prepared for her.</i>

1851
01:29:10,436 --> 01:29:14,201
<i>Except the last thing
she said was,</i>

1852
01:29:14,303 --> 01:29:15,609
<i>"It is not real."</i>

1853
01:29:15,711 --> 01:29:18,241
...not... real...

1854
01:29:18,343 --> 01:29:20,979
Maybe she was trying
to tell us

1855
01:29:21,081 --> 01:29:23,481
that the miracle wasn't real.

1856
01:29:25,355 --> 01:29:26,319
Ah.

1857
01:29:27,549 --> 01:29:29,188
You see what I mean when I say

1858
01:29:29,290 --> 01:29:31,622
something happened
that you didn't expect?

1859
01:29:31,724 --> 01:29:35,060
I think you gave her a script,
and she went off the book,

1860
01:29:35,162 --> 01:29:36,791
and now you're
trying to recover.

1861
01:29:38,968 --> 01:29:40,762
Well, if that's right,
then, uh,

1862
01:29:42,030 --> 01:29:44,634
there'd have to be another way
into this basement, yeah?

1863
01:29:45,742 --> 01:29:46,768
Shall we have a look?

1864
01:29:47,942 --> 01:29:50,112
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1865
01:29:54,212 --> 01:29:55,480
I don't think there is.

1866
01:29:56,078 --> 01:29:57,516
No.

1867
01:29:57,952 --> 01:29:59,751
I'm not doing very well,

1868
01:29:59,853 --> 01:30:01,288
Sister Paxton.

1869
01:30:01,722 --> 01:30:03,491
Unless...

1870
01:30:03,593 --> 01:30:04,621
(WATER DRIPPING)

1871
01:30:12,901 --> 01:30:14,895
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1872
01:30:22,546 --> 01:30:23,508
(RATTLING)

1873
01:30:32,755 --> 01:30:34,717
(WATER POURING)

1874
01:30:35,691 --> 01:30:37,654
(WATER DRAINING)

1875
01:30:50,073 --> 01:30:52,273
- (CLANKING)
- (MUSIC STOPS PLAYING)

1876
01:30:54,237 --> 01:30:56,409
(CREAKING)

1877
01:31:02,917 --> 01:31:04,450
Which means that...

1878
01:31:05,750 --> 01:31:07,216
there would have to be
a dead body down there

1879
01:31:07,318 --> 01:31:08,952
if you were right, huh?

1880
01:31:09,054 --> 01:31:10,425
PAXTON: Correct.

1881
01:31:11,127 --> 01:31:12,524
MR. REED: How will you
test your theory?

1882
01:31:13,159 --> 01:31:14,559
(SIGHS) I don't know.

1883
01:31:15,594 --> 01:31:18,131
MR. REED: But will you go
into that hole and

1884
01:31:18,233 --> 01:31:19,831
see if there's
somebody down there?

1885
01:31:19,933 --> 01:31:21,302
If I have to.

1886
01:31:22,137 --> 01:31:23,370
MR. REED: Why would you
do that?

1887
01:31:25,140 --> 01:31:28,076
Because I want
to know the truth,

1888
01:31:28,178 --> 01:31:30,443
and because the only way out
is through.

1889
01:31:31,681 --> 01:31:32,709
Robert Frost?

1890
01:31:33,342 --> 01:31:34,546
<i>Swamp Thing.</i>

1891
01:31:35,146 --> 01:31:36,548
(CHUCKLES)

1892
01:31:38,053 --> 01:31:39,485
Don't go into that cellar...

1893
01:31:41,319 --> 01:31:42,991
unless you are prepared

1894
01:31:43,093 --> 01:31:44,990
to discover the one,
true religion.

1895
01:31:45,092 --> 01:31:47,295
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1896
01:31:56,036 --> 01:31:58,240
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

1897
01:31:59,038 --> 01:32:00,407
(SNIFFLES)

1898
01:32:02,141 --> 01:32:04,279
(LADDER CREAKS)

1899
01:32:11,987 --> 01:32:13,948
(RISING SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

1900
01:32:18,356 --> 01:32:20,023
- (MUSIC STOPS)
- (SIGHS)

1901
01:32:20,125 --> 01:32:21,857
(FOOTSTEPS)

1902
01:32:29,332 --> 01:32:30,772
I knew it.

1903
01:32:30,874 --> 01:32:32,538
(DOOR CREAKS AND SLAMS)

1904
01:32:36,912 --> 01:32:39,114
(HEAVY BREATHING)

1905
01:32:39,216 --> 01:32:41,382
- (WATER SPLASHING)
- (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1906
01:32:49,024 --> 01:32:50,922
(LOCK CREAKS AND CLICKS)

1907
01:32:51,024 --> 01:32:52,855
(DOOR CREAKS)

1908
01:32:57,594 --> 01:32:59,763
(CONTINUES HEAVY BREATHING)

1909
01:33:04,534 --> 01:33:06,737
(UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING)

1910
01:33:12,045 --> 01:33:13,777
(DOOR CREAKS)

1911
01:33:25,190 --> 01:33:26,757
(SHARP INHALE)

1912
01:33:28,326 --> 01:33:30,563
(DOOR CREAKING)

1913
01:33:35,937 --> 01:33:37,702
(WATER DRIPPING)

1914
01:33:40,173 --> 01:33:42,410
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1915
01:33:50,416 --> 01:33:52,618
(CONTINUES HEAVY BREATHING)

1916
01:33:57,555 --> 01:33:59,790
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1917
01:34:12,841 --> 01:34:14,105
(GASPS)

1918
01:34:14,207 --> 01:34:15,773
(HEAVY BREATHING)

1919
01:34:21,148 --> 01:34:22,751
(MUSIC FADES OUT)

1920
01:34:22,853 --> 01:34:24,782
(DOOR CREAKING)

1921
01:34:28,219 --> 01:34:29,154
(CLANK)

1922
01:34:29,256 --> 01:34:30,517
(DISTANT WEAK WHEEZING)

1923
01:34:30,619 --> 01:34:32,158
(SHUDDERING BREATH)

1924
01:34:32,260 --> 01:34:34,088
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1925
01:34:43,807 --> 01:34:45,803
(COUGHING)

1926
01:34:46,337 --> 01:34:48,304
(FAINT GROANING)

1927
01:34:48,406 --> 01:34:50,775
(SHIVERING BREATH)

1928
01:34:55,817 --> 01:34:56,814
Hey.

1929
01:35:01,352 --> 01:35:02,655
(SNIFFLES)

1930
01:35:07,194 --> 01:35:08,155
(PAXTON SHIVERING)

1931
01:35:13,729 --> 01:35:15,635
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1932
01:35:20,439 --> 01:35:22,171
Sorry about the cold.

1933
01:35:22,274 --> 01:35:23,478
(SNIFFLES)

1934
01:35:24,807 --> 01:35:26,111
Have you figured it out yet?

1935
01:35:26,213 --> 01:35:27,174
(PAXTON SNIFFLES)

1936
01:35:29,886 --> 01:35:31,079
I think so.

1937
01:35:33,089 --> 01:35:34,148
MR. REED: So what is it?

1938
01:35:35,358 --> 01:35:39,894
What is the one,
true religion, Sister P?

1939
01:35:39,996 --> 01:35:41,059
(PAXTON SHIVERING)

1940
01:35:41,161 --> 01:35:42,862
(SNIFFLING)

1941
01:35:42,964 --> 01:35:43,960
It's...

1942
01:35:47,397 --> 01:35:48,602
(INHALES)

1943
01:35:49,599 --> 01:35:51,104
(HEAVY BREATHING)

1944
01:35:51,206 --> 01:35:53,472
When we first arrived,

1945
01:35:53,574 --> 01:35:55,672
you left us alone
in your living room.

1946
01:35:55,774 --> 01:35:57,709
(DRAMATIC, SUSPENSEFUL
MUSIC PLAYING)

1947
01:35:57,811 --> 01:35:59,973
<i>We thought you were talking
to your wife,</i>

1948
01:36:00,075 --> 01:36:02,517
<i>but you were doing
something else.</i>

1949
01:36:03,314 --> 01:36:04,617
I was.

1950
01:36:04,719 --> 01:36:07,652
PAXTON: You took a key
from Sister Barnes' coat,

1951
01:36:07,755 --> 01:36:11,119
went outside to unlock
our bikes and hide them.

1952
01:36:15,632 --> 01:36:17,961
<i>I noticed your hair was wet
when you came back</i>

1953
01:36:18,063 --> 01:36:21,161
<i>with the drinks, like you were
out in the storm.</i>

1954
01:36:21,263 --> 01:36:23,071
You did this, I assume,
because you didn't want

1955
01:36:23,173 --> 01:36:23,930
the Elder to find our bikes

1956
01:36:24,032 --> 01:36:25,268
when he came back
looking for us.

1957
01:36:25,370 --> 01:36:26,506
(LATCH CLANKS)

1958
01:36:26,608 --> 01:36:28,206
But there was something else
on your mind.

1959
01:36:28,308 --> 01:36:29,310
(WATER POURING)

1960
01:36:29,412 --> 01:36:31,513
- There was.
- (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1961
01:36:33,009 --> 01:36:34,412
PAXTON: <i>You returned
the bike key</i>

1962
01:36:34,514 --> 01:36:36,751
<i>to the wrong coat pocket.</i>

1963
01:36:37,521 --> 01:36:39,448
<i>We thought this was a mistake
you made.</i>

1964
01:36:39,550 --> 01:36:40,720
(MOUTHING) Key.

1965
01:36:42,152 --> 01:36:44,087
PAXTON: (VOICE SHAKING)
But now I know it wasn't.

1966
01:36:44,189 --> 01:36:45,485
Why?

1967
01:36:45,587 --> 01:36:46,691
(INHALES)

1968
01:36:46,794 --> 01:36:50,026
You gave the bike lock
to one of your prophets,

1969
01:36:50,128 --> 01:36:53,598
instructed them to lock
the final cellar door with it.

1970
01:36:53,700 --> 01:36:56,769
But why, why, why?
Why did I do that?

1971
01:36:57,669 --> 01:36:59,605
Because you wanted me to know

1972
01:36:59,708 --> 01:37:02,571
the only reason
I'm standing here right now

1973
01:37:02,673 --> 01:37:04,410
is because it is exactly

1974
01:37:04,512 --> 01:37:06,680
where you want me
to be standing.

1975
01:37:07,582 --> 01:37:09,813
I'm not here
because I chose to be.

1976
01:37:09,915 --> 01:37:12,247
I'm here because you made me
choose to be.

1977
01:37:12,349 --> 01:37:13,688
Oh.

1978
01:37:13,790 --> 01:37:18,122
Because you want me to believe
the one, true religion is...

1979
01:37:18,224 --> 01:37:20,026
(SIGHS)

1980
01:37:20,128 --> 01:37:21,321
...control.

1981
01:37:25,397 --> 01:37:27,167
(CHUCKLES)

1982
01:37:27,269 --> 01:37:28,867
That is exactly right.

1983
01:37:31,133 --> 01:37:34,301
Religion is just
a system of control...

1984
01:37:35,011 --> 01:37:36,606
(WHEEZING)

1985
01:37:36,708 --> 01:37:38,440
(HEAVY BREATHING)
It's okay.

1986
01:37:38,542 --> 01:37:39,779
I'll help you.

1987
01:37:39,881 --> 01:37:41,115
MR. REED: No, you see,
that's what's so interesting.

1988
01:37:41,217 --> 01:37:43,010
They don't want your help.

1989
01:37:43,112 --> 01:37:45,119
They... (CHUCKLING)
they are exactly

1990
01:37:45,221 --> 01:37:46,285
where they chose to be.

1991
01:37:46,387 --> 01:37:47,748
But you killed that woman.

1992
01:37:47,850 --> 01:37:48,950
MR. REED: I disagree.

1993
01:37:49,052 --> 01:37:51,489
She... She chose to eat
a poisoned pie

1994
01:37:51,591 --> 01:37:53,526
because of her profound faith.

1995
01:37:53,628 --> 01:37:57,427
It is called drinking the...
anyone?

1996
01:37:57,529 --> 01:37:59,262
(SNAPPING SHEARS)

1997
01:37:59,364 --> 01:38:00,561
Kool-Aid.

1998
01:38:00,663 --> 01:38:02,095
It is true...

1999
01:38:02,197 --> 01:38:04,633
that I keep these ladies
a little chilly,

2000
01:38:04,735 --> 01:38:05,836
and a little peckish,

2001
01:38:05,938 --> 01:38:07,907
for which I am very sorry.
Sorry, ladies.

2002
01:38:08,443 --> 01:38:09,969
But only for the same reason

2003
01:38:10,071 --> 01:38:11,544
that your church goes to Haiti

2004
01:38:11,646 --> 01:38:14,115
to give out Bibles
after a hurricane.

2005
01:38:14,217 --> 01:38:16,681
It's easier to control

2006
01:38:16,783 --> 01:38:18,715
- someone who has lost...
- (SHEARS CLICK)

2007
01:38:18,817 --> 01:38:20,015
- ...everything.
- (SHEARS CLICK)

2008
01:38:20,117 --> 01:38:22,016
You're absolutely right.
She did go off-book.

2009
01:38:22,118 --> 01:38:24,553
- (SHEARS SLICE)
- (PROPHET SCREAMS)

2010
01:38:24,655 --> 01:38:26,389
Why do you do this?

2011
01:38:26,491 --> 01:38:28,129
The question is,

2012
01:38:28,231 --> 01:38:29,930
why do you all let me?

2013
01:38:30,032 --> 01:38:30,965
(SPLASH)

2014
01:38:31,067 --> 01:38:32,359
(WHIMPERING)

2015
01:38:33,168 --> 01:38:34,564
(WHEEZING)

2016
01:38:34,666 --> 01:38:36,636
PAXTON: Sorry... (CRYING)

2017
01:38:36,738 --> 01:38:38,738
You are here
because the ideas of others

2018
01:38:38,840 --> 01:38:40,808
have influenced every single
decision you've made

2019
01:38:40,910 --> 01:38:43,337
since the day you were born,
and I've been able to predict

2020
01:38:43,439 --> 01:38:45,639
every decision you would make
tonight because of that.

2021
01:38:45,741 --> 01:38:47,308
(WHIMPERING)

2022
01:38:48,383 --> 01:38:50,377
- (CRYING)
- (SHUSHING)

2023
01:38:53,619 --> 01:38:54,851
You have allowed them

2024
01:38:54,953 --> 01:38:57,056
to dictate
every decision of your life.

2025
01:38:57,158 --> 01:38:58,688
(CRYING)

2026
01:38:58,790 --> 01:39:02,529
They decide who you worship,

2027
01:39:02,631 --> 01:39:05,161
where you worship,
what you worship.

2028
01:39:05,263 --> 01:39:07,461
- (PAXTON BREATHING HEAVILY)
- (SPRINKLER SPRAYING)

2029
01:39:07,563 --> 01:39:11,365
They even dictate the garments
you wear under your clothes.

2030
01:39:12,536 --> 01:39:13,741
The what?

2031
01:39:15,311 --> 01:39:16,808
Your magic underwear.

2032
01:39:16,910 --> 01:39:18,172
- (SLASHING)
- (MR. REED SCREAMS, GURGLES)

2033
01:39:18,275 --> 01:39:20,341
- (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)
- (PAXTON PANTING)

2034
01:39:22,382 --> 01:39:24,686
(GROANING)

2035
01:39:27,552 --> 01:39:29,922
(SQUELCHING)

2036
01:39:30,752 --> 01:39:32,185
(PANTING)

2037
01:39:32,287 --> 01:39:34,091
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING)

2038
01:39:47,805 --> 01:39:50,140
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

2039
01:39:56,679 --> 01:39:58,885
(PANTING)

2040
01:39:59,287 --> 01:40:01,118
(GRUNTING)

2041
01:40:04,786 --> 01:40:06,057
(GROANS)

2042
01:40:10,597 --> 01:40:12,833
(OMINOUS MUSIC BUILDS)

2043
01:40:13,863 --> 01:40:15,198
(MUSIC FADES OUT)

2044
01:40:17,205 --> 01:40:18,938
(PANTING)

2045
01:40:21,508 --> 01:40:23,844
(DOOR CREAKING)

2046
01:40:29,781 --> 01:40:31,951
(UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING)

2047
01:40:32,849 --> 01:40:34,188
(HEAVY BREATHING)

2048
01:40:34,290 --> 01:40:35,482
(DOOR CREAKING)

2049
01:40:39,327 --> 01:40:40,720
No... No...

2050
01:40:40,822 --> 01:40:41,789
No...

2051
01:40:41,891 --> 01:40:43,759
(HEAVY BREATHING)

2052
01:40:43,861 --> 01:40:45,228
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

2053
01:40:51,540 --> 01:40:53,775
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

2054
01:41:17,629 --> 01:41:19,526
(SQUELCHING)

2055
01:41:21,401 --> 01:41:22,830
(GASPS)

2056
01:41:22,932 --> 01:41:24,839
(PAXTON WHIMPERS)

2057
01:41:25,438 --> 01:41:27,275
(CLATTER)

2058
01:41:27,377 --> 01:41:29,206
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

2059
01:41:30,071 --> 01:41:31,505
(PAXTON WHIMPERING)

2060
01:41:35,278 --> 01:41:36,979
- (DOOR SLAMMING SHUT)
- (PAXTON GASPS)

2061
01:41:37,081 --> 01:41:39,381
- (PANTING)
- (MR. REED GROANING)

2062
01:41:46,625 --> 01:41:48,159
(WHEEZING)

2063
01:41:48,593 --> 01:41:49,558
(GROANS)

2064
01:41:49,660 --> 01:41:50,627
(LAUGHS)

2065
01:41:50,729 --> 01:41:52,198
(PAXTON WHIMPERING)

2066
01:41:52,301 --> 01:41:53,296
(GROANING)

2067
01:41:54,029 --> 01:41:55,331
(EXHALES HEAVILY)

2068
01:41:56,472 --> 01:41:58,203
(GROANS, INHALES SHARPLY)

2069
01:41:58,705 --> 01:42:00,206
MR. REED: (WEAKLY) Pray...

2070
01:42:00,309 --> 01:42:01,403
(WHIMPERS)

2071
01:42:03,179 --> 01:42:04,142
Pray.

2072
01:42:04,940 --> 01:42:07,147
(WATER DRIPPING)

2073
01:42:07,250 --> 01:42:09,048
(WHIMPERS)

2074
01:42:10,814 --> 01:42:12,381
Pray for us.

2075
01:42:13,849 --> 01:42:15,285
(EXHALES)

2076
01:42:16,856 --> 01:42:18,720
Praying... (INHALES SHARPLY)

2077
01:42:18,822 --> 01:42:20,459
...doesn't work.

2078
01:42:20,561 --> 01:42:22,061
(BREATHING WEAKLY)

2079
01:42:23,696 --> 01:42:24,693
(PAINED BREATH)

2080
01:42:24,795 --> 01:42:26,560
(PAXTON PANTING)

2081
01:42:26,662 --> 01:42:30,135
Have you ever heard of
the great prayer experiment?

2082
01:42:31,967 --> 01:42:33,767
(GRUNTING)

2083
01:42:33,869 --> 01:42:35,874
(GROANS)

2084
01:42:35,976 --> 01:42:38,109
They divided patients
into groups.

2085
01:42:38,211 --> 01:42:41,883
Those who received prayers
and those who didn't.

2086
01:42:45,447 --> 01:42:48,087
The results of the study
were conclusive.

2087
01:42:48,555 --> 01:42:50,221
It doesn't work.

2088
01:42:51,054 --> 01:42:52,120
But I think it's beautiful

2089
01:42:52,222 --> 01:42:53,954
that we all pray
for each other...

2090
01:42:54,056 --> 01:42:55,322
(MR. REED GROANS)

2091
01:42:55,424 --> 01:42:57,696
...even though
we all probably know

2092
01:42:57,798 --> 01:42:59,626
it doesn't make a difference.

2093
01:43:00,567 --> 01:43:02,366
(WHEEZING)

2094
01:43:02,468 --> 01:43:06,138
It's just nice to think about
someone other than yourself.

2095
01:43:08,136 --> 01:43:09,537
Even if it's you.

2096
01:43:12,710 --> 01:43:13,981
(GROANS)

2097
01:43:15,682 --> 01:43:16,951
(BREATHING WEAKLY)

2098
01:43:19,418 --> 01:43:22,122
- (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)
- (PAXTON PRAYING INDISTINCTLY)

2099
01:43:22,792 --> 01:43:24,558
...I'm grateful
for all the trials

2100
01:43:24,660 --> 01:43:26,323
you've given me in my life.

2101
01:43:28,030 --> 01:43:30,925
And for your path
that you've laid out for me.

2102
01:43:31,027 --> 01:43:34,067
(WHEEZING) Quietly.

2103
01:43:39,640 --> 01:43:41,173
(MR. REED WHIMPERS)

2104
01:43:42,445 --> 01:43:43,271
(MR. REED WHEEZES)

2105
01:43:43,373 --> 01:43:45,207
(PAXTON CONTINUES
PRAYING INDISTINCTLY)

2106
01:43:45,309 --> 01:43:47,476
(DRAMATIC MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING)

2107
01:44:00,595 --> 01:44:03,030
(INDISTINCT PRAYER)

2108
01:44:04,900 --> 01:44:05,898
- (MUSIC STOPS PLAYING)
- (SLASHING)

2109
01:44:06,000 --> 01:44:07,128
- (MR. REED GROANS, SCREAMS)
- (GASPS)

2110
01:44:07,230 --> 01:44:09,498
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

2111
01:44:16,105 --> 01:44:18,540
(BREATH TREMBLING)

2112
01:44:21,112 --> 01:44:23,380
(SLOW, DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

2113
01:44:53,145 --> 01:44:55,544
(SOMBER INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

2114
01:44:57,487 --> 01:44:59,680
(IMPERCEPTIBLE)

2115
01:45:11,194 --> 01:45:13,397
(WATER DROPS PATTERING)

2116
01:45:15,900 --> 01:45:17,434
Goodbye, Sister.

2117
01:45:20,608 --> 01:45:21,603
(SNIFFLES)

2118
01:45:23,379 --> 01:45:24,377
(KISSES)

2119
01:45:24,479 --> 01:45:25,574
(SOBBING)

2120
01:45:26,308 --> 01:45:28,282
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

2121
01:45:28,384 --> 01:45:30,810
(PANTING)

2122
01:45:33,181 --> 01:45:34,352
(WHIMPERS)

2123
01:45:43,896 --> 01:45:46,100
(CONTINUES PANTING)

2124
01:45:49,670 --> 01:45:50,764
(CREAKING)

2125
01:46:02,817 --> 01:46:04,844
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

2126
01:46:12,021 --> 01:46:14,293
(PANTING)

2127
01:46:37,687 --> 01:46:39,813
(DRAMATIC MUSIC RISES)

2128
01:46:41,152 --> 01:46:42,720
(MUSIC STOPS PLAYING)

2129
